author: ETA PRIME
description:
Meet the Teenage Engineering Computer-2—a free, flat-pack PC case you download, cut, and fold into a real Mini-ITX build. It’s weird, it’s odd… and it’s awesome. In this video, I build a full Mini-ITX rig inside the Computer-2, walk through the assembly, and test thermals, noise, and real-world gaming to see if a $0 case can actually hang.
